            My name is Claire Meuter and I’m an environmental data
            scientist interested in using data analysis and
            visualization to explore the diverse ecological, economic,
            and social challenges facing our planet. I am especially
            passionate about land planning and conservation, and using
            data science and visualization to inform conservation
            decisions.
            I am currently a second-year MESM student at the UCSB
            Bren School.
